    <body>
        
        <div xml:id="Kali7-kilavi">
          <p type="edition">itu, pirivuṇarttappaṭṭa tōḻi talaimakaṟku nīr pirikiṉṟīreṉṟu 
            yāṉ kūṟat talaivi kēṭpiṉ avaṭku akkālattu nikaḻvaṉavaṟṟai nummōṭu ārāyvatuṭaiyēṉ; 
            nīr ceyyum poruḷ ivaḷ uyiraiyun taru-kiṟkumō eṉac celavaḻuṅkak kūṟiyatu.
            </p>
          <p type="translation" xml:lang="en"/>
        </div>
        <div xml:id="Kali7-kilavi2">
            <p type="edition">iḵtu “uṭaṉ cēṟal ceykaiyō ṭaṉṉavai piṟavu – maṭampaṭa vanta tōḻi kaṇṇum” 
        <note>(to.po.146, l. 43f.)</note> eṉpataṉuṭ ceykai kūṟukiṉṟatu.</p>
        </div>
        <div xml:id="Kali7">
            <lg type="edition">
                <l>vēṉi luḻanta vaṟituyaṅ kōykaḷiṟu</l>
                <l>vāṉīṅku vaippiṉ vaḻaṅkāttēr nīrkkavāaṅ</l>
                <l>kāṉaṅ kaṭatti reṉakkēṭpiṉ yāṉoṉ</l>
                <l>ṟucāvukō vaiya ciṟitu;</l>
                <l rend="space">nīyē, ceyviṉai maruṅkiṟ celavayarn tiyāḻaniṉ</l>
                <l>kaipuṉai valviṉ ñāṇuḷar tīyē</l>
                <l>ivaṭkē, ceyvuṟu maṇṭila maiyāp patupōṉ</l>
                <l>maiyil vāṇmukam pacappū rummē;</l>
                <l rend="space">nīyē, viṉaimāṇ kāḻakam vīṅkak kaṭṭip</l>
                <l>puṉaimāṇ marīiya vampu teritiyē;</l>
                <l rend="space">ivaṭkē, cuṉaimā ṇīlaṅ kāretir pavaipō</l>
                <l>liṉainōk kuṇkaṇ ṇīrnil lāvē;</l>
                <l rend="space">nīyē, pulampi ṉuḷḷamoṭu poruḷvayiṟ celīiya</l>
                <l>valampaṭu tikiri vāynī vutiyē;</l>
                <l rend="space">ivaṭkē, alaṅkitaḻk kōṭal vīyuku pavaipō</l>
                <l>lilaṅkē relvaḷai yiṟaiyū rummē;</l>
                <l rend="space">eṉaniṉ,</l>
                <l>ceṉṉavai yaravattu miṉaiyava ṇīnīppiṟ</l>
                <l>ṟaṉṉalaṅ kaṭaikoḷap paṭutaliṉ maṟṟiva</l>
                <l>ḷiṉṉuyir tarutalu māṟṟumō</l>
                <l>muṉṉiya tēettu muyaṉṟucey poruḷē.</l>
            </lg>
            <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>            If I hear that you would cross the forest,</l>
<l>where the sadly weakened, tired elephant bull that bore the summer</l>
<l>longs for water that is a chariot that does not move (i.e., a mirage) in the region left by the clouds,</l>
<l>would I help one little bit, o lord?</l>
<l rend="space">You, engaged in going for the work to be done,</l>
<l>you would smooth the string of your hand-made strong bow.</l>
<l rend="space">For her, like the active orb’s becoming dim</l>
<l>pallor will creep over [her] spotless bright face.</l>
<l rend="space">You, tying tautly the glove glorious for [its] work[manship],</l>
<l>would test the arrow in which the glorious of [its] make come together.</l>
<l rend="space">For her, like the glorious blue lotus in the pools that face the rainy season,</l>
<l>water in [her] kajal eyes with desperate glance won’t stand still.</l>
<l rend="space">You, in order to go on account of wealth with a heart free from loneliness,</l>
<l>you would stroke the rim of [your] victorious discus.</l>
<l rend="space">For her, like blossoms of Malabar glory lily with swaying petals that are shed,</l>
<l>shining, fine, bright bangles would creep over [her] joints. </l>
<l rend="space">That is, </l>
<l>if you leave her who is like this at the sound of your going-fault,</l>
<l>because her goodness would be brought to an end, is she</l>
<l>able to give [her] sweet life too,</l>
<l>for the wealth to the made with effort in [foreign] countries, as [you] plan?  </l>
            </lg>
        </div>
